body:
You can use the MongoDB Search [faceted navigation](fts-facet-ref) collector to extract
metadata and avoid running multiple queries for search results and
metadata. You can use `$search.facet` to retrieve both documents
and metadata in a single query. If you only need metadata,
use `$searchMeta.facet` to avoid document lookup. For an example,
see the [Metadata and Search Results Example](fts-facet-egs).

Using a [$limit](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/limit) aggregation pipeline stage after a
[$facet](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/facet) aggregation pipeline stage might negatively impact query performance. To avoid
performance bottlenecks, use [$limit](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/limit) before
[$facet](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/facet).

> **Example:**&#x20;
>
> ```json
> {
>   {
>     "$search": {...}
>   },
>   { "$limit": 20 },
>   {
>     "$facet": {
>       "results": [],
>       "totalCount": $$SEARCH_META
>     }
>   }
> }
> ```

For a demonstration, see the following examples:

- [Metadata and Search Results Example](fts-facet-egs)

- [Facet Example](fts-count-aggregation-variable)
